Key Match Events: Austria scored the opening goal after Donyell Malen deflected the ball into his own net
Cody Gakpo equalized for the Netherlands with a curling shot
Romano Schmid scored Austria's second goal with a diving header
Memphis Depay scored the Netherlands' first goal after a VAR review
Marcel Sabitzer scored Austria's third goal following a defensive mistake by the Netherlands
Post-Match Reflections: Ralf Rangnick's young, hungry side stormed past the Dutch to secure top spot in Group D
The Dutch defenders were outnumbered and struggled to contain Austria's attacks
The Dutch tried to rally but failed to capitalize on their chances
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was marked by a high tempo and insolent play from Austria
The Austrian fans were ecstatic after their team's victory
Others: The result means France, Portugal, Germany, and Spain are all in one side of the knock-out draw
The Dutch team will have to regroup and prepare for the next round
